steps.detailed_description: Load the following tables as inputs: part (p_partkey, p_name, ...), lineitem (l_orderkey, l_partkey, l_suppkey, l_quantity, l_extendedprice, l_discount, ...), orders (o_orderkey, o_orderdate, ...), supplier (s_suppkey, s_nationkey, ...), partsupp (ps_partkey, ps_suppkey, ps_supplycost, ...), nation (n_nationkey, n_name, ...). All columns are read to enable downstream joins and calculations.
Join part with lineitem on p_partkey = l_partkey to attach item details to each lineitem. Input: part and lineitem. Output: intermediate_dataset_A containing fields from both tables.

Join intermediate_dataset_A with orders on l_orderkey = o_orderkey to associate each lineitem with its order (and order date). Input: intermediate_dataset_A and orders. Output: intermediate_dataset_B.

Join intermediate_dataset_B with supplier on l_suppkey = s_suppkey to link each lineitem to its supplier. Then join with nation on s_nationkey = n_nationkey to bring in nation context and with partsupp on p_partkey = ps_partkey AND s_suppkey = ps_suppkey to obtain supply cost information. Input: intermediate_dataset_B + supplier + nation + partsupp. Output: intermediate_dataset_C containing all necessary fields for profit calculation and grouping.

Filter to parts where p_name LIKE '%green%' (case-insensitive as appropriate). Compute per-lineitem profit: profit = l_extendedprice * (1 - l_discount) - ps_supplycost * l_quantity. Extract year from o_orderdate. Output: dataset with fields nation, year, and computed profit for each relevant lineitem.
Group by nation name and order year, and aggregate the profit to obtain total profit per nation per year. Output: aggregated_dataset with columns: n_name (nation), o_year (year), total_profit.
Write the aggregated results to a text file as the final output.
